Coastal
For the coastal region, we observe a 121.25 MW increase in generation capacity (an increase of approximately 22.8 percent) between 2011 and 2021. The following figure shows the change in total installed capacity for each prime mover in the coastal region. This region saw additions of 38.9 MW of fossil turbines, 28.9 MW of reciprocating engines, and 53 MW of renewable energy and storage capacity.

c_cap = FileAttachment("data/coastal-capacity.csv").csv({ typed: true })

Plot.plot({
