Railbelt
For the Railbelt region, capacity additions were dominated by more-efficient fossil fuel generating units and new battery storage. These additions are shown in Figure X and Figure X. There were 762 MW of capacity additions between 2011 and 2021. The Railbelt region saw 207 MW of reciprocating engine additions and 390 MW of fossil fuel turbines. The remaining capacity additions were renewables and storage and are shown in Figure X.

